% Slide: What is a system of equations?
\begin{frame}{What is a System of Equations?}
  \begin{itemize}
    \item A system of equations is a set of two or more equations with the same variables.
    \item We look for a solution that satisfies all equations simultaneously.
    \item In two variables (usually $x$ and $y$), a system of linear equations is:
    \[
    \begin{cases}
    a_1x + b_1y = c_1 \\
    a_2x + b_2y = c_2
    \end{cases}
    \]
    \item The solution is the point $(x, y)$ where the two lines intersect.
  \end{itemize}

